        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Higher Education",
          "Blended Learning",
          "End of Course Performance",
          "Pass (>=5) vs Fail (<5)",
          "591 students",
          "3 compulsory university courses: Physical Chemistry I, Physics III, Analytical Chemistry Laboratory",
          "LMS logs, Student characteristics, Learner grades",
          "[Gender; forum views; page views; resource views; folder views; URL views; assignment views; assignment grades; course total views; course total activity]",
          "Monthly early prediction during semester; 6 cumulative snapshots from Feb to Jul (except Physical Chemistry I starts in March)",
          "Custom Moodle plugin exported cumulative monthly reports. Students with no access to an activity received 0. No missing values. Final grade was transformed into nominal pass/fail. Auto-WEKA search space was restricted to tree- and rule-based classifiers for interpretability.",
          "Naïve Bayes, Random Forest, Bagging, PART, SMO, IBk-5NN, Auto-WEKA over Decision Stump, J48, LMT, REPTree, Random Tree, OneR, JRip, PART, M5Rules, M5P",
          "10-fold Cross-Validation",
          "Best AutoML results:\n{Accuracy: 0.9302 - Auto-WEKA LMT for Analytical Chemistry Lab (June/July)}",
          "Main contribution is showing that AutoML improves early pass/fail prediction over default ML settings while keeping models interpretable by limiting the search to rule/tree-based learners. LMT was the most frequent Auto-WEKA winner.",
          "Single institution and only 3 courses. Results depend on cumulative course-specific Moodle reports and assignment grades. AutoML training is slower and sensitive to time limits. No demographic variables beyond gender."
        ],
        [
          "Regression",
          "Higher Education",
          "Blended Learning",
          "End of Course Performance",
          "inal grade (0–10)",
          "591 students",
          "3 compulsory university courses: Physical Chemistry I, Physics III, Analytical Chemistry Laboratory",
          "LMS logs, Student characteristics, Learner grades",
          "[Gender; forum views; page views; resource views; folder views; URL views; assignment views; assignment grades; course total views; course total activity]",
          "Monthly early prediction during semester; 6 cumulative snapshots from Feb to Jul (except Physical Chemistry I starts in March)",
          "Custom Moodle plugin exported cumulative monthly reports. Students with no access to an activity received 0. No missing values. Final grade kept as continuous 0–10 target. Feature-importance analysis with ExtraTrees showed assignment-grade features were more informative than view counters for regression. Auto-WEKA search restricted to tree/rule-based methods.",
          "Random Forest, M5Rules, Bagging, SMOreg, IBk-5NN, Auto-WEKA over tree/rule-based learners including M5P, REPTree, Random Tree, M5Rules",
          "10-fold Cross-Validation",
          "Best AutoML results:\n{MAE = 1.0402 – M5P for Analytical Chemistry Lab (June)}",
          "AutoML improved regression performance in all cases. Tree-based regressors dominated the best Auto-WEKA solutions, especially M5P and Random Tree. Assignment grades were stronger predictors than simple access counters.",
          "Same limitations as above; results are course-specific and depend strongly on assignment information. AutoML time budget affects the selected model. Small number of courses."
        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Higher Education",
          "Blended Learning",
          "Dropout",
          "Dropout vs No Dropout",
          "462 students for modeled courses",
          "2 compulsory university courses: Physical Chemistry I and Physics III",
          "LMS logs, Student characteristics, Learner grades",
          "[Gender; forum views; page views; resource views; folder views; URL views; assignment views; assignment grades; course total views; course total activity]",
          "Monthly early prediction during semester; 6 cumulative snapshots from Feb to Jul (except Physical Chemistry I starts in March)",
          "Same custom Moodle export procedure. Dropout defined as missing final grade. Because Analytical Chemistry Lab had only 6% dropout, it was excluded from this task due to severe class imbalance. ROC was used instead of accuracy. Auto-WEKA optimized “area above ROC”.",
          "Naïve Bayes, Random Forest, Bagging, PART, SMO, IBk-5NN, Auto-WEKA over tree/rule-based learners including Decision Stump, J48, Random Tree, LMT",
          "10-fold Cross-Validation",
          "Best AutoML results:\n{AUC = 0.928 – LMT for Physical Chemistry I (June)}",
          "AutoML again outperformed default learners. For dropout, tree-based methods were the only Auto-WEKA winners, with LMT the most frequent. Feature importance for dropout involved the widest variety of features among the three tasks.",
          "Only 2 courses modeled for dropout. Class imbalance constrained the analysis and excluded one course. Dropout operationalization as empty final grade may miss nuanced disengagement patterns."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
